modules.description: This module processes and transforms map-related expressions in OCaml code during compilation. It works with abstract syntax trees (ASTs) and map data structures, specifically handling key-value associations. Concrete use cases include rewriting map literals and operations into optimized core OCaml expressions.

This module defines configuration options for expanding `let` expressions in OCaml syntax extensions. It includes boolean flags to control whether to open modules during expansion (`do_open`) and whether to collapse sequential binds (`collapse_binds`). Specific configurations like `default`, `default_open`, `n`, and `n_open` provide predefined combinations for common use cases in let-binding transformations.

This module transforms `let` expressions and related constructs in OCaml ASTs during compilation, supporting operations like bind, map, and match expansion. It works with value bindings, expressions, and patterns, primarily manipulating syntax tree nodes from Ppxlib. Concrete use cases include rewriting monadic binds, optimizing map expressions, and generating efficient code for pattern matching and destructuring.
